=== 国庆期间 ===
新加坡政府鼓励民众在[[新加坡国庆日|新加坡国庆日]]期间在住宅或公司的窗前、门前悬挂国旗；特别是一些[[组屋|组屋]]区，区域政府会鼓励住户在窗外悬挂国旗，有时整栋组屋楼的住家都会挂出新加坡国旗<ref>{{cite journal|last=Leong|first=Laurence Wai-Teng|title=Consuming the Nation: National Day Parades in Singapore|url=http://www.nzasia.org.nz/downloads/NZJAS-Dec01/Leong.pdf|format=PDF|journal=New Zealand Journal of Asian Studies|volume=3|issue=2|date=December 2001|page=5 at 14|publisher=The New Zealand Asian Studies Society|accessdate=2007-11-03|author=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070716205119/http://www.nzasia.org.nz/downloads/NZJAS-Dec01/Leong.pdf|archive-date=2007-07-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2007年的新加坡国庆日上，有8667名志愿者在政府大厦大草场手举红色或白色的雨伞，组成了一幅迄今为止最大的新加坡国旗<ref>{{cite web|title=Mass participation— communities: Largest national flag formed by umbrellas|url=http://www.singaporebookofrecords.com/singapore_records_individual.php?id=NjAwMDAwMTk5Nw|publisher=The Singapore Book of Records|date=2007-08-09|accessdate=2007-11-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080512181936/http://www.singaporebookofrecords.com/singapore_records_individual.php?id=NjAwMDAwMTk5Nw|archive-date=2008-05-12|dead-url=yes}} {{cite web|title=Think BIG on National Day 2007!|url=http://www.youngntuc.org.sg/nationalday/index.asp|publisher=Young NTUC|date=2007-08-09|accessdate=2007-11-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071011060200/http://youngntuc.org.sg/nationalday/index.asp|archive-date=2007-10-11|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

=== 平日 ===
[[File:Singapore_flags_and_banners_in_Istana_Park_-_20080817.jpg|thumb]]
国庆期间以外，新加坡国旗一般出现在与政府相关的大楼门外，例如住房部、移民部、教育部等。新加坡教育院校中也都会升有新加坡国旗，在教室里，白板上方都会放置一面新加坡国旗，这种在教室中悬挂的国旗多为[[塑料|塑料]]制品。小学和中学每周都至少会举行一次升旗仪式，学生们被要求在升旗过程中唱[[前进吧，新加坡|国歌]]并宣读[[新加坡国家信约|信约]]<ref>See, for instance, the following: para. 22 of {{cite web|last=Lee|first=Hsien Loong|authorlink=|title=National Education: Speech by BG Lee Hsien Loong, Deputy Prime Minister at the launch of National Education on Saturday 17 May 1997 at TCS TV Theatre at 9.30 am|url=http://www.moe.gov.sg/media/speeches/1997/170597.htm|publisher=Ministry of Education|date=1997-05-17|accessdate=2007-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080430070230/http://www.moe.gov.sg/media/speeches/1997/170597.htm|archive-date=2008-04-30|dead-url=yes}} Paragraph 18 of {{cite web|last=Teo|first=Chee Hean|authorlink=|title=Getting the fundamentals right: Speech by RADM (NS) Teo Chee Hean, Minister for Education and Second Minister for Defence at the NIE Teachers Investiture Ceremony at 2.30 pm on 8 Jul 2003 at the Singapore Indoor Stadium|url=http://www.moe.gov.sg/media/speeches/2003/sp20030708.htm|publisher=Ministry of Education|date=2003-07-08|accessdate=2007-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090306012515/http://www.moe.gov.sg/media/speeches/2003/sp20030708.htm|archive-date=2009-03-06|dead-url=yes}} Paragraph 3 of {{cite web|title=Press release: Submission of proposals for privately-funded schools|url=http://www.moe.gov.sg/media/press/2006/pr20060605.htm|publisher=Ministry of Education|date=2006-06-05|accessdate=2007-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080507130158/http://www.moe.gov.sg/media/press/2006/pr20060605.htm|archive-date=2008-05-07|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

[[File:RedEnsignofSingapore-20051226-cropped.jpg|thumb]]
有时一些在新加坡注册的海上船只也会悬挂新加坡国旗，但这种行为是不正确的，正确的做法是在船只上悬挂新加坡[[海上用旗|民船旗]]。新加坡民船旗为全红底，中央有一圆圈，包裹着新月和五颗星<ref>Section 37(1) of the. A master of a Singapore ship who fails without reasonable cause to comply with this section is guilty of an offence and is liable on conviction to a fine not exceeding S$1,000: s. 37(2). If any distinctive national colours other than the government ensign are hoisted on board any Singapore ship without official consent, the master of the ship or the owner if on board the ship— as well as every other person hoisting the colours— are guilty of an offence, and are liable on conviction to a fine not exceeding S$1,000: s. 36(2).</ref>。海巡舰艇或军用舰艇同样不悬挂国旗，而是悬挂新加坡海军旗<ref name=MPA>{{cite web|author=Lee Seng Kong (Director of Marine)|title=National colours for Singapore ships (MC No. 13 of 1999)|url=http://www.mpa.gov.sg/sites/port_and_shipping/circulars_and_notices/shipping_circulars_detail.page?filename=mc99-13.xml|publisher=Maritime and Port Authority of Singapore|date=1999-07-20|accessdate=2008-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110525095447/http://www.mpa.gov.sg/sites/port_and_shipping/circulars_and_notices/shipping_circulars_detail.page?filename=mc99-13.xml|archive-date=2011-05-25|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。新加坡的民船旗、政府船旗、军舰旗分别以英国[[红船旗|红船旗]]、[[蓝船旗|蓝船旗]]、[[白船旗|白船旗]]参考而设计。

国家若出现严重事故、重要人士逝世或举行[[全国哀悼日|国家哀悼日]]时，全国的国旗会被要求[[半旗|降半旗]]<ref name=halfstaff>{{cite book|title=Our Army Customs and Traditions|url=http://www.mindef.gov.sg/imindef/resources/e-books/ebklist.-imindefPars-0022-DownloadFile.tmp/ourArmyCustomsTraditions.pdf|location=Singapore|publisher=Ministry of Defence|year=2006|pages=130–131|access-date=2011-10-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081003120704/http://www.mindef.gov.sg/imindef/resources/e-books/ebklist.-imindefPars-0022-DownloadFile.tmp/ourArmyCustomsTraditions.pdf|archive-date=2008-10-03|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。新加坡国旗曾在前总统或资政逝世时降过半旗<ref>For instance, after the death of former Second Deputy Prime Minister (1980–1985) and later Senior Minister (1985–1988) S. Rajaratnam on 22 February 2006, the national flag was flown at half-mast on all government buildings from 23 February to 25 February 2006.</ref>，2005年1月9日，为纪念在[[2004年印度洋大地震|2004年印度洋大地震]]逝世的人们，新加坡政府决定破例降半旗<ref>A national minute of silence was also observed on that date after a memorial service at about 6:00 pm, marked by the sounding of Public Warning System alerts by the Singapore Civil Defence Force (SCDF): {{cite web|title=One minute of silence to be observed throughout Singapore; SCDF will sound alert|url=http://getformesingapore.com/previous2005/090105_singaporeobservesoneminuteofsilencetoday.htm|publisher=Ministry of Community Development, Youth and Sports (republished on Getforme Singapore Online)|date=2005-01-07|accessdate=2007-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071023184851/http://www.getformesingapore.com/previous2005/090105_singaporeobservesoneminuteofsilencetoday.htm|archive-date=2007-10-23|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

===文化===
[[新加坡|新加坡]]作曲家林宇中在1969年曾作过名为《五星旗升起》的曲，这首歌曲的歌词便是从新加坡国旗五颗星中获取的灵感，歌词中曾提到“新月、五星从海平面上升起……新月代表着年轻，带给人们希望……每颗星都像一个向导，指引着我们前进……红色的旗帜代表着人类的鲜血，白色代表着纯洁和自由。”民众也经常会在[[新加坡国庆日|新加坡国庆日]]上演唱这首歌曲<ref>{{cite web|title=Five Stars Arising|url=http://www.singsingapore.org.sg/songs-lyric.asp?sid=27|publisher=Sing Singapore|year=2005|accessdate=2007-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927232449/http://www.singsingapore.org.sg/songs-lyric.asp?sid=27|archive-date=2007-09-27|dead-url=yes}} See also List of Singaporean patriotic songs.</ref>。

2003年，新加坡媒体发展管理局（MDA）禁止新加坡艺术家李志剛展出一幅名为“双喜”的[[油画|油画]]。这幅油画中画有新加坡国旗，国旗上写有[[汉字|汉字]]“双喜”。新加坡媒体发展管理局禁止展出这幅油画的理由是新加坡国旗是国家的象征，任何字或图都不允许加在国旗上。而李志剛则回应称他的作品只是简单的表现出新加坡的成功给民众带来喜悦。在接受《[[我报|我报]]》采访时李志剛称：我知道作为一个新加坡公民是不被允许做这种事的，但我始终认为这只是艺术的表现。他同时抱怨政府对此类事情似乎有双重标准，因为中国艺术家谷文达也曾在[[滨海艺术中心|滨海艺术中心]]创作了一个用头发组成的新加坡国旗艺术品<ref name="teo">{{cite news|last=Teo|first=Faith|title=Art on the flag: A publicity stunt?|url=http://newpaper.asia1.com.sg/printfriendly/0,4139,14410,00.html|publisher=''The New Paper''|date=2003-01-25|accessdate=2007-11-04|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071112123219/http://newpaper.asia1.com.sg/printfriendly/0,4139,14410,00.html|archivedate=2007-11-12|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。同年，[[滚石乐队|滚石乐队]]来到新加坡进行全球巡演。第一场演出中，设计人员在舞台上布置了两个[[性爱娃娃|性爱娃娃]]，在它们的裆部覆有图案，其中一只性爱娃娃的图案是滚石乐队的标志，另一个则是新加坡国旗<ref>{{cite book | last = Millard | first = Mike | authorlink = | coauthors = Ivan Hall | title = Jihad in Paradise: Islam and Politics in Southeast Asia | publisher = M. E. Sharpe | year = 2004 | location = | pages = 125 | url = http://books.google.com/?id=JTmqmSkqIFcC&pg=PA125&lpg=PA125&dq=The+Rolling+Stones+Singapore+flag&q=The%20Rolling%20Stones%20Singapore%20flag | doi = | id = | isbn = 978-0-7656-1336-3 }}</ref>。因为被告知这时非法使用新加坡国旗，设计人员在第二场演出中移除了这两个性爱娃娃<ref>{{cite book | last = Boehme | first = Olaf | authorlink = | coauthors = Gerd Coordes, Chris Jagger | title = The Rolling Stones: Fruit of the Loom Tour ; Licks World Tour 2002/2003 | publisher = Books on Demand GmbH| date = 2005-06 | location = Norderstedt| pages = 120 | url = http://books.google.com/?id=5cKWx5_TNqIC&pg=PA120&dq=The+Rolling+Stones+Singapore+flag&cd=2#v=onepage&q=The%20Rolling%20Stones%20Singapore%20flag | doi = | id = | isbn = 3-8334-2857-0 }}</ref>。

2007年8月，一个新加坡夜店向至少1500名会员发送了一封广告邮件<ref>{{cite news | first=Alexis | last=Ong | coauthors= | authorlink= | title=The Insider – the national flag | date=2008-08-18 | publisher=Time Out Group Ltd | url=http://www.timeoutsingapore.com/aroundtown/feature/the-insider-the-national-flag | work=Time Out Singapore | pages= | accessdate=2009-11-30 | language= | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716220118/http://www.timeoutsingapore.com/aroundtown/feature/the-insider-the-national-flag | archive-date=2011-07-16 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。邮件中是一位性感美女穿着红色泳衣和泳裤，衣物上的图案组成了五颗星。这家夜店称这是国庆庆典期间的广告促销手段，其经理对媒体称：“这个广告绝对不是对国旗或对其他个人的侮辱，我认为这则广告能象征这幽默和娱乐精神。”新加坡新闻通讯及艺术部了解到此事后进行了调查，最后得出结论，称这家夜店并没有违反相关法律，因为夜店的广告只是含有一部分国旗元素。尽管如此，新加坡新闻通讯及艺术部的负责人还是对媒体称：艺术部虽不会取缔此类广告，但也绝不鼓励，每个人都应该对国旗保持应有的尊重<ref>{{cite news|last=Au Yong|first=Esther|title=Popular bar slammed for cheeky use of stars & crescent of S'pore flag|url=http://newpaper.asia1.com.sg/printfriendly/0,4139,138442,00.html|publisher=''The New Paper''|date=2007-08-12|accessdate=2007-11-04|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071112123213/http://newpaper.asia1.com.sg/printfriendly/0,4139,138442,00.html|archivedate=2007-11-12|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

